# Implementation Plan - Estate-Driven Ideology & Journey Testing

## Goal
Elevate the ideological simulation by replacing the static `overton_radius` with a dynamic model driven by **Interest Group (Estate)** influence and happiness. Concurrently, refactor the engine into a library/binary split and establish a 100% coverage-focused integration test suite.

> [!CAUTION]
> ### RADICAL ARCHITECTURAL PIVOT: Estate-Driven Ideology
> The [IdeologyComponent](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/state.rs#26-31) will no longer be direct state targets for most actions. Instead, actions will target **Interest Groups (Estates)**, and country-level Ideology/Overton Window will be **derived** during the Chronos tick.
> - **Rationale**: To reflect real-world political friction where the "Acceptable" zone is a product of competing power centers.
> - **Impact**: `overton_radius` is deprecated. UI will derive the window from the spread and influence of Estates.

## Proposed Changes

### [brinkmanship_engine]

#### [MODIFY] [state.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/state.rs)
- **[NEW]** `Estate` struct: `{ name: String, influence: f64, happiness: f64, alignment: (f64, f64) }`.
- **[NEW]** `InterestGroupsComponent`: `HashMap<String, Estate>`.
- **[MODIFY]** [IdeologyComponent](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/state.rs#26-31): Replace `overton_radius` with `center: (f64, f64)` and `spread: f64`.

#### [MODIFY] [chronos.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/chronos.rs)
- **Estate Resolution**: Apply [PendingAction](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/state.rs#52-62) to specific estates.
- **Overton Calculation**:
  - `Center = Σ(Alignment * Influence) / Σ(Influence)`
  - `Spread = sqrt(Σ(Influence * (Alignment - Center)^2) / Σ(Influence))`
- This ensures the "Acceptable" zone expands/contracts based on polarization and influence shifts.

#### [MODIFY] [chronos.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/chronos.rs)
- **Estate Resolution**: Apply [PendingAction](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/state.rs#52-62) to specific estates (Happiness/Influence).
- **Ideology Derivation**: 
  - `center = WeightedMean(Estates.alignment by influence)`.
  - `spread = StandardDeviation(Estates.alignment weighted by influence)`.
- Re-calculate `active_phase` based on average happiness/stability.

#### [NEW] [journey_tests.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/tests/journey_tests.rs)
- **"The Populist Surge" Journey**:
  1. Initialize state with influential "Lower Class" estate.
  2. Apply "Economic Stimulus" (Target: Lower Class, Happiness +10).
  3. Advance 5 turns.
  4. Verify the `IdeologyComponent.center` shifts toward the "Planned" axis.

### [Documentation & Meta]

#### [MODIFY] [AI_RULES.md](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/AI_RULES.md)
- Ensure Rule 0 (Testing) and Rule 10 (Disclosure) are finalized.

#### [MODIFY] [FUTURE_WORKS.md](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/docs/FUTURE_WORKS.md)
